<scriptment id="49000" point="e3_notify" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-08-13" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki holds to her face a letter.</narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="letter" voicelang="en">Dear Ms. Takeshi,</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="letter" voicelang="en">The 2011 Electronic Entertainment Expo's cancellation&#x2014;</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="letter" voicelang="en">Is null and void!</line>
		<line id="4000" speaker="letter" voicelang="en">We hope to see Sega and its newest, hottest products two months from now,</line>
		<narration>Yuki looks at the calendar. Two months from August 13, 2011 &#x2014;</narration>
		<line id="4000" speaker="letter" voicelang="en">On August 17, 2011.</line>
		<narration>Yuki tears the paper and kicks the chair and almost flips a table but Shimizu slams the table back in place and yells at her, primal fear in her eyes. Yuki yells at everyone.</narration>
		<line id="5000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">E3's not cancelled the show is in four days we need to show them a game&#x2014;</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="hanako" voicelang="ja">Like the one we started two weeks ago?</line>
		<narration>Yuki slams her hands together. She whimpers.</narration>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Nozomi.</line>
		<narration>From the far far corner of the big big studio enters Nozomi.</narration>
		<line id="8000" speaker="nozomi" voicelang="ja">Yes, honey?</line>
		<line id="9000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">E3's coming. Welcome to the Cold War.</line>
		<line id="10000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Our game is not presentable.</line>
		<line id="11000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">It needs to look like it is.</line>
		<line id="12000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="ja">Catch my drift?</line>
		<line id="13000" speaker="nozomi" voicelang="ja">I'll have the screenshots and videos ready next week.</line>
		<narration>Nozomi rushes off. Yuki lays on the ground, wide-eyed but dead-faced.</line>
		<line id="14000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">The industry isn't destroying the medium.</line>
		<line id="15000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">The medium is destroying the industry.</line>
	</part>
</scriptment>